⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Shai-Hulud
node D1 · D1 · ⟦Shai-Hulud:D1:6f5746⟧

WHO   — Shai-Hulud — the sandworms, the Old Man of the Desert
WHAT  — The colossal sandworms of Arrakis, ancient beasts that rule the deep desert and produce the spice through their life-cycle.
WHERE — D1 · Dune  Framework inputs: The cosmology of Arrakis — the living engine of the spice  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — As the planet's living engine they are the source of the spice — and in Leto II's hybrid form, the vessel through which a man becomes a god and the spice is reborn.
HOW   — Drawn by rhythm and destroyed by water, they rise from the sand to be ridden by the Fremen as Maker; their cycle gives the spice.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  The desert moves, and the world is reborn within its passing.

